    • Method Detail

      • find

        public boolean find()
        Find the next instance of the Pattern in the data text. After the method executes, the current state of the matcher will update to the current circumstances.
        Returns:
        Returns whether or not the Pattern was found.

      • group

        public java.lang.String group()
        Get the text that was matched the current time. The find method has to have been called at least one time prior to the invocation of this method.
        Returns:
        The String representing the Pattern that was matched in the find() method call.

      • start

        public int start()
        Get the start index of the match at the current time. The find method has to have been called at least one time prior to the invocation of this method.
        Returns:
        The start index of the match at the current time.

      • end

        public int end()
        Get the end index of the match at the current time. The find method has to have been called at least one time prior to the invocation of this method.
        Returns:
        The end index of the match at the current time.

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Reset the values of the Matcher. This will make the find method start from the beginning again.
